ZH: 血液流淌在我的体内。
EN: Blood flows through my body.

ZH: 他受伤了，血流了很多。
EN: He is injured and bleeding a lot.

ZH: 这种药可以净化血液。
EN: This medicine can purify the blood.

ZH: 捐献血液可以拯救生命。
EN: Donating blood can save lives.

ZH: 鲜血染红了整个地板。
EN: Fresh blood has stained the entire floor red.

ZH: 血液检测显示他患有贫血。
EN: Blood tests show that he has anemia.

ZH: 血液循环是人体健康的关键。
EN: Blood circulation is crucial for overall health.

ZH: 他粗心大意，划破了手指让血流了出来。
EN: He was careless and cut his finger, causing blood to flow out.

ZH: 血缘关系很重要，不仅仅是亲属关系。
EN: Blood relation is important, not only for family ties.

ZH: 血肉之躯是指人的身体。
EN: The "flesh and blood" of a person refers to the physical body.

ZH: 继续流血可能导致他丧失意识。
EN: Continued bleeding may cause him to lose consciousness.

ZH: 血液外流不止，他伤势很严重。
EN: The blood keeps flowing out, his injury is severe.

ZH: 血是人体里非常重要的液体。
EN: Blood is a very important fluid in the human body.

ZH: 血统可以向我们追溯到多久以前的祖先。
EN: Bloodline can be traced back to our ancestors from long ago.

ZH: 血压高容易导致心脏疾病。
EN: High blood pressure can lead to heart disease.

ZH: 血缘关系不应该决定一个人的价值。
EN: Blood relations should not determine a person's worth.

ZH: 血氧浓度的测量可以很好地反映人体的健康状况。
EN: Measuring blood oxygen levels can effectively reflect the health status of the body.

ZH: 流血不止需要及时处理。
EN: Continuous bleeding needs to be treated promptly.

ZH: 血统之争导致了家族的矛盾。
EN: Conflict over bloodline caused discord within the family.

ZH: 母亲的血液型决定了孩子的血型。
EN: The blood type of the mother determines the blood type of the child.
